<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q22_v3" title="Q22_v3" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>En cualquier prisma recto de base rectangular, el cuadrado de la longitud de la diagonal espacial es igual a la suma de los cuadrados de las longitudes de sus tres aristas.</p>
    <p>Considera un prisma recto de base rectangular cuya diagonal espacial mide <m:math><m:msqrt><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math> cm y dos de sus aristas miden 5 cm y 8 cm.</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>¿Cuánto mide la arista faltante?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        
        9 cm
      <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si la arista faltante midiera 9 cm, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>9</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>81</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>170</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero el cuadrado de la diagonal espacial es <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:msqrt><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>170</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, 9 cm no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        6 cm
      <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La diagonal espacial cumple <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>36</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Entonces el cuadrado de la diagonal es 125 y la diagonal mide <m:math><m:msqrt><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math> cm, exactamente como dice el enunciado.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        
        10 cm
      <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si la arista faltante midiera 10 cm, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>100</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>189</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero el cuadrado de la diagonal espacial debe ser <m:math><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>189</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, 10 cm no es la arista faltante.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        
        11 cm
      <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Si la arista faltante midiera 11 cm, entonces <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>11</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>121</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>210</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>. Pero el cuadrado de la diagonal espacial es <m:math><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:math>. Como <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>210</m:mn><m:mo>≠</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math>, 11 cm no cumple la condición del problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
  <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
    <qti-content-body>
      <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Paso 1: Escribir la relación dada en el enunciado</strong></p>
          <p>En un prisma recto de base rectangular, el cuadrado de la diagonal espacial es igual a la suma de los cuadrados de las tres aristas.</p>
          <p>Si la arista faltante es <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>, entonces:</p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:msqrt><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Paso 2: Calcular los cuadrados conocidos</strong></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:msqrt><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p>Reemplazando:</p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>125</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Paso 3: Sumar y despejar</strong></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>25</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>64</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>89</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p>Entonces:</p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>125</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>89</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>125</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>89</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Paso 4: Obtener la longitud de la arista</strong></p>
          <p><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msqrt><m:mn>36</m:mn></m:msqrt><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></p>
          <p>Como se trata de una longitud, se toma el valor positivo.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
          <p>La arista faltante mide 6 cm.</p>
          <p>La alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </qti-content-body>
  </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>